Text.Value: A few moonrises back, I thought the answer was complicated. But it's quite simple, really:
As if you needed to ask.
We'll have our chance. I'm sure of it.
I've changed my mind. I still want to be together.
Fortune willing, as the seasons of life pass into winter and my hair goes to grey, you'll still be within my quivering arm's reach.
I - I don't know what to say.
I'm glad. I want that too.
So be it.
And one day, I might even call you consort to Grand Duke Wyll Ravengard of Baldur's Gate. My pride, my joy.
Surely.
It's over, Wyll.
May I kiss you?
Ah. How to answer a question with so many layers as that?
On to other topics.
I saw our future in my dreams: grand adventures, tender moments, and all the wonders in between them.
Ah. You're the author of your own story. You get to choose which part I play.
You are my yesterday, my today, and my tomorrow.
I want nothing more. Unique as your heart might be, I still feel it tugging at mine.
My favourite subject.
You make a damn fun dance partner, too.
You are the red of the sunrise, the yellow of high noon, and the orange of sundown. If you were a song, I'd never stop singing; if you were a psalm, I'd never stop praying.
Just do me a favour - make it a story worth telling, a life worth living. You deserve nothing less.
I wish I could kiss you, Wyll.
I know. But until that day comes, I'm content just knowing you're near.
What am I to you?
May I kiss you?
No more kisses, no more dances. I want to be allies, nothing more.
I'll let you go if I must, without crying or complaint - but with the gratitude that I could know the happiness of us.

Synopsis: Default dialogue when speaking to Wyll during exploration.
